  "prompt": "How does the legal system address complex money laundering schemes?",
  "response": "Legal systems address money laundering through various laws, investigative techniques, and international cooperation. Strategies typically include:\n\n1. Legal frameworks\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) requirements\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n\n2. Investigative approaches\n- Financial transaction tracking\n- Forensic accounting\n- Collaboration between law enforcement agencies\n- Using advanced technological tools\n\n3. International cooperation\n- Mutual legal assistance treaties\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n\n4. Prevention mechanisms\n- Bank reporting requirements\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Background checks\n- Asset seizure provisions\n\nI aim to provide objective information about legal approaches to financial crime without endorsing specific actions.",
